Preconditions:
The input matrix `mat` is not null.
The input matrix `mat` has at least one element.
The input matrix `mat` is a 2D array with dimensions `m x n`.
The input matrix `mat` is 0-indexed.
No two adjacent cells in the matrix `mat` are equal.

Postconditions:
The method returns a length 2 array `[i, j]` where `i` represents the row index and `j` represents the column index of a peak element in the matrix `mat`.
The returned array `[i, j]` represents the position of any peak element in the matrix `mat`.